2.00	Hsu_Feng	Hsu Feng	Hsu Feng is a Chinese actress, producer and business manager. In the 1970s she was one of the leading actresses of the cinemas of Hong Kong and Taiwan, in particular being known for her roles in wuxia movies and her work with the director King Hu. In 1981 she retired from her career as an actress, but a few years later she returned to the movies as a producer. For her production of Chen Kaige's Farewell My Concubine she received the Palme d'Or (1993) and the BAFTA Award for Best Film not in the English Language (1994).	
